<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-09-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="290" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-09-24"><hi rend="italic">September 24,
                                    1897</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Have visited foreign office to urge early date for Bering Sea conference.
                            Promise reply. Have expressed my disagreement with conclusion of British
                            Government about Russia and Japan, and await your further
                            instructions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>